headline: CLSE: Long-Short ETF Ahead Of The Competition
summary: Since Convergence Long/Short Equity ETF was listed in February 2022, it has outperformed the S&P 500 and a number of long-short ETFs. Moreover, it was resilient in the 2022 market downturn.

headline: AppLovin, MicroStrategy, and 28 Other Stocks That Could Be Bubbles
summary: In a research note published Wednesday, 22V Research’s head of technical strategy, John Roque, shared 30 names that are currently trading at more than 100% above their 200-day moving averages.  Stocks priced at that level are often “exhibiting bubble-like tendencies,” he said.  “It’s not that these stocks can’t go up again, because they can,” Roque wrote.

headline: Does Billionaire Israel Englander Know Something Wall Street Missed? He Sells Nvidia Stock and Buys an AI Stock Up 2,260% Since 2022
summary: Billionaire Israel Englander is the CEO of Millennium Management, the second-most profitable hedge fund in history in terms of net gains since inception, according to LCH Investment.  Englander sold 1.6 million shares of Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA), cutting his position by 13%.  Nvidia stock returned 705% over the last two years.
